S/W Installation Guide (CPU)


By Prof. Seungchul Lee

Industrial AI Lab at POSTECH

Table of Contents

1. Overview¶

  • Contents
    • deals with installment of packages for machine learning and deep learning

  • OS

    • Even though TensorFlow packages are somehow proper in Linux type of OS,
    • This manual provides you in Windows 10 for users' convenience

  • GPU

    • TensorFlow enables to utilize GPU parallel computing with CUDA
    • This manual handles CPU version's installment for convenience
  • Anaconda
    • This manual doesn't use Anaconda to prevent collapsing between the packages

2. Requirements¶

  • Windows 10, 64 bits PC (recommended)
  • Python 3.7.2
  • Visual C++ 2015 Redistributable (or 2017)
  • Wheel files
    • fastcache, ecos
  • Cautions
    • Windows display language should be in English
    • Delete Python or Anaconda if already installed
  • Installation files
    • You can download all installation files including wheel files from the link below.
    • https://www.dropbox.com/sh/o0axet5wgyvz1c2/AAA9zE-PU9H7X1qaJAePvO3va?dl=1

3. Cautions¶

3.1. Windows 사용자명이 한글인 경우 (For Korean Students)¶

[1] 시작 $\rightarrow$ 다른 사용자 추가, 편집 또는 제거 검색

[2] 이 PC에 다른 사용자 추가

[3] 이 사람의 로그인 정보를 가지고 있지 않습니다 클릭

[4] Microsoft 계정 없이 사용자 추가 클릭

[5] 사용자명 입력 (영문, 띄어쓰기 X)

[6] 다음

[7] 계정 유형 변경

[8] 관리자 선택

[9] 시작 메뉴에서 계정 아이콘 클릭

[10] 새로 만든 계정으로 로그인


3.2. If another version of Python or Anaconda installed¶

[1] Search $\rightarrow$ Advanced system settings

[2] Click 'Environment Variables'


[3] Delete all paths including python or anaconda shown below

[4] Select user/system variable path

[5] Select environment variables with python or anaconda

[6] Click 'Delete'

4. Environment Setup¶

  • Get the installation files from the right link and make sure to unzip the files in the same directory

  • Visual C++ 2015 Redistributable
    • Install vc_redist.x64.exe as attached
    • It doesn't need to be installed if the window shown in the right pops up

5. Python and its Packages Installation¶

  • Python installation

    [0] Run python-3.6.0-amd64.exe

    [1] Uncheck the first box and check the second one

    [2] Click 'Install Now'

  • Package installation

    [3] Run command window with administrator privileges

    [4] Change directory to the directory where the installation files are located

    [5] Run the following command pip install --upgrade pip

    [6] Run the following command pip install numpy scipy

    [7] Run the following command pip install toolz six seaborn scs scikit_learn pillow pandas matplotlib ipython dill jupyter tensorflow

    [8] Copy the following command and paste it into the command window

    pip install ecos-2.0.7.post1-cp37-cp37m-win_amd64.whl fastcache-1.0.2-cp37-cp37m-win_amd64.whl

6. Setup Validation¶

  • Running Jupyter Notebook

    [1] Type 'Jupyter notebook' in folder's domain

  • Create Jupyter Notebook

    [2] Click 'New'

    [3] Select 'Python 3'

  • Running code

    [4] Run the code after typing as below

    $\;\;\;\;$ Available by clicking the button or also with Ctrl+enter
